---
title: Mean Reversion Trading Strategy
tags:
  - quantitative research
  - finance
  - stock market

---

Mean reversion in the stock market refers to the idea that stock prices that are trading higher (or lower) than their historical prices will revert to their long-term historical mean. Mean reversion trading strategy takes advantage of this information, to trade stocks that significantly deviate from their historical means to profit from the short-term price fluctuations.

